<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 10:13PM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern St.
Joseph County through 1045 PM EDT...
At 1013 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Centreville, or 7 miles northeast of Three Rivers, moving east at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Colon.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
